## EHR

### Unified Practice

1. Run a report for: Reports -> Patient Summary -> Export
2. Drag report to pipeline/client-data/paom/raw/unifiedpractice
3. Rename to MM-DD-YYYY
4. $ pnpm run pipeline:ehr-preprocess paom // Normalize patients
5. $ pnpm run pipeline:patients-to-db paom // Patients to db (upsert)
6. $ pnpm run pipeline:fetch-contacts paom // Fetch contacts from GHL
7. $ pnpm run pipeline:contacts-to-db paom // Leds to DB
8. $ pnpm run pipeline:link-patients paom // link patients

### Thrive

1. Chirotouch -> Chirotouch Front Desk (from the big hand menu) -> Billing statements & Reports -> Reports -> New patient list -> Preview-> Select all -> Next -> Export -> new-patients-02-28-2026.xls (name is important). It doesn't matter how far back you export as long as it overlaps w/ a previous import it will ensure all new patients are added
2. Ensure the process is done for for Belmar & Thrive
3. $ pnpm run pipeline:ehr-preprocess thrive // Normalize patients - Since there are two locations, it will process ALL files with the latest date. If one date is behind the other it will only process the most recent.
4. $ pnpm run pipeline:patients-to-db thrive // Patients to db (upsert)
5. $ pnpm run pipeline:fetch-contacts thrive // Fetch contacts from GHL
6. $ pnpm run pipeline:contacts-to-db thrive // Leds to DB
7. $ pnpm run pipeline:link-patients thrive // link patients
